,Recommended,238320,32283587,Posted: 8 June,all,bazongle,"""I am not recommending this game due to the fact that it is nothing but jumpscares. There is no story, and it is just cheap, scripted events. If you want a good game, with awsome story, play Five Nights at Freddys!""                 -an actual Steam review, 2016NOTE: I made sure to complete this game before writing my review. This is also a spoiler free review. Please enjoy! :)------------------The Story--------------This game has to be the scariest game I've played in my life. The scares are unexpected, and the tension of being chased, and getting into a door/vent at the last moment is just, ""OHHHHHHHHHHHH!"" It is just so well done! This is probably due to the fact that it's developed by Red Barrels, who have worked on multiple very successful games! They are very good in this field of game. The big devs should get into this kinda stuff. Sorry, going off track!------------------Gameplay and AI-----------The hiding mechanics are amazing! Enimies are obvoiusly on a random data table, for searching through lockers and bed, (ex. there are 27 beds, the AI will check 2 random ones, leave and check back later.) Enimies are smart enough to flank you, go around doors, and even juke you basketball style!------------------Scares----------------------This game perfectly blends scripted scares and non-scripted scares. When an enemy sees you, and the intense chase music starts playing, you know you're screwed! I should also mention that this is a mature, MATURE game. There are some shocking scenes! All in all, the scares and shocks work hand in hand to make a terrifying game!-----------------Characters------------------These are some people you are not gonna forget these phycos! I'll start by saying your character is a mute. An interesting thing is that you do know with this guy is thinking by him writing notes. This is genius, because we are with him the whole , and after a scary event, we get to read his input on that event. I really like this! This is an amazing addition to the silent protagonist. And the inmates, again, no spoilers! You. Will. Not. Forget. Them.-----------------The Verdict/TLDR-----------------This is one of the best modern horror games out there, and besides a few VERY minor glitches, this is one healthy baby boy! This games get my strongest 10/10. And I don't give this a lot of the time!"
