76561198034978223,Recommended,238320,30299790,Posted: 3 March,all,Cassar1709,"This is one of the best horror games out there.First and foremost the sound of the game is probably the best I have ever seen in any game. The amount of detail that can be heard when wearing high quality headphones is impressive and it makes the experience very realistic, besides helping the player project where the enemies are in the darkness of the Asylum.The graphics are incredible. In some parts of the game, you can stare at a certain spot and think: 'What in this image makes me know that it's a game and not real life?' And a lot of times you can't come up with an answer, that's how realistic the graphics look especially with the night vision on the camera.The voice acting is another one of the strong spots of this game. The screams and speeches of the patients sound extremely convincing, making the player question whether those are the screams of actors or actually insane patients. That combined with the high sound quality and amazing graphics makes Mount Massive Asylum a very real place and makes playing the game a more than enjoyable experience.On the other hand, the game lacks a little in story. Not to say that the story is bad, but the dynamics of the game makes the player sometimes forget what he's doing since he's too worried in not dying or getting caught. In other words, it's easy to forget your current objective. This is a very common mistake in horror games, but since Outlast is not very long and since every other aspect is overwhelmingly well done, the lack in story is overlooked by most players.It doesn't hurt to mention that the player will never feel safe during the game, unlike other games with 'safe spots' such as Resident Evil 7. That forces you to take breaks during the gameplay; it's not easy to clear this game in one sitting even though the game is not very long. The game ends just when it's about to become repetitive so the lenght feels perfect. Not too long and not too short.In summary, Outlast is one of the best horror games ever made and it is definitely worth your money if you're looking for something that will keep you up at nights for a while. It's not recommended, though, for those easily frightened and that don't know what they're getting themselves into. 10/10"
