,Recommended,238320,11293788,"Posted: 17 July, 2014",all,Pakkidis,"Rating: 8.5/10What is it?First Person Survivor HorrorThe Good:+ The games main objective is to scare the living crap out of you and it succeeds on so many levels. The combination of music, atmosphere, graphics all lead up to a very frightening experience.+Great atmosphere. The game takes place mostly in an Asylum.+Graphically, the game is gorgeous. The game makes good use of darkness, forcing you to use a camcorder with night vision to help navigate the environment.+ The gameplay although basic gets the job done. You have no method of combat so you have to rely on stealth, running, peaking around corners to avoid enemies.  The focus is on exploration and solving basic puzzles.+ Music is very well done, really adds to the horror element.+Decent story, most of it is done through records scattered around the levels.+Good length for the type of game. It doesn't wear itself out.The Bad:-The biggest problem I found was that the game relies on the same puzzles throughout most of the game. I.e Find 2 switches, levers, buttons to progress. Overtime it doesn't feel 'natural' to the setting but it starts feeling repetitive.-The AI can feels a bit wonky at times. It becomes hard to predict when they come after you and when they don't and what triggers it.ConclusionIf you've played Amnesia or Slenderman you should know what to expect with this game. The goal is to get absorbed into the world, and try and survive until the end. Your ultimate enjoyment is going to depend on how scared you are going to be and how interested you are in the story.  The length isn't a big issue, as I was able to complete the game in roughly 4 hours. Its a solid length for the game as anything longer and it would start feeling very tedious. I highly recommend this game if your looking for a  good horror game."
