,Recommended,238320,29249913,Posted: 14 January,all,KuroiSenko,"Outlastknows how to create tension and creepy atmosphere. It may not contain a lot of jumpscares (only few) but in this case they're not necessary because everything else related to horror is pretty much on point. Hence, some spare pants or sedatives may be needed afterwards.The storyrevolves around a journalist who decides to investigate a remote psychiatric hospital. Armed with nothing but a camera you progress through creepy hallways, sewers and bloody hospital chambers. The asylum is surrounded by darkness with only a few exceptions. Your only way of seeing in the dark is to use the night vision setting in your camera which requires a constant battery change (you can find them scattered in random spots). As you learn more about the incident throughout the game, you can find out even more by collecting documents and completing recordings.Sound effectsin both horror games and movies are obviously essential for a  good thrill. Outlast has top notch sounds, ranging from simple door creaking and running on different surfaces to sobbing and screaming in agony.The musicis also great and fits the genre well, however, I couldn't hear the dialogue for the most part as you can't adjust the music volume at all. Overall, it's a quite short game, requiring around4 hoursto finish it, so I'd recommend buying this on sale.P.S. do yourself a favor and play late at night with lights off and headphones on.7.5/10"
