,Recommended,238320,16578497,"Posted: 21 June, 2015",all,Biodegradable,"Outlast is a game that will make you afraid of the dark. Not only is it terrifying thanks to an utterly disturbing atmosphere, finely-crafted jumpscares (yes, it can be done) and a forboding musical score, it's also relentless and will never let you rest. Need a breather? Too bad, cos the psychopath behind you wants to wear your head like a hat, and he ain't gonna take no for an answer. You reckon you've been in a situation game-wise that made you feel completely helpless? Unless you've played Outlast, you don't know squat, pal.Now some reckon that Outlast is a tad overrated, usually pointing out the flawed story and questioning why the protagonist doesn't simply leave the asylum. But honestly, in an era where every other horror game has either fallen victim to trends, turned themselves into an action-adventure game (looking at you, Resident Evil), or given up the ghost completely, this phenomenal game is a welcome return to decent, principled horror. Red Barrels (the development team) understands tension, atmosphere, and knows how to leave you beaten,  bloody, bruised, and begging for more.It's a staggeringly beautiful, lovingly crafted and deliciously creepy game that has well earned the praise it has received. Any self-respecting horror fan will have this gem nestled among the rest of their collection."
