,Not Recommended,238320,32732976,Posted: 24 June,all,dawhoopmaster,"Where do I start? This game isn't scary in the slightest (alright, mayne the Walrider is) but other than that, this game lacks fear, other than when you play it for the first time and fell scared out of uncertainty.Chase sequences are frequent and repetative, and are usually always having you followed by Chris Walker, there is very little enemy variety.Green was always my favourite colour, but after this, I'm honestly sick of it. It's a horror game, it's dark, I respect that. And since there's a camera, night vision was an effective way to let players roam the darkness. But this has to be used so often my eyes got tired of just seeing green everywhere.Going back to what I said about chase sequences, there more repetative gameplay to talk about. It's either ""Find a key (or other object) or  ""Turn on valves"" or ""Hide from Chris Walker.""This next one isn't necesseraly a problem, but don't buy this expecting you'll have plenty to play. I'll admit, I didn't finish it, but from what I've seen of gameplay videos, I'm pretty close. Yet I only started playing this morning, and since I've got an exam next week I haven't been playing all day.And finally, if you've watched AVGN you may recognise the term ""this is one of those where the f*ck do I go kinda games."" This sums up Outlast. Constant running around the same area trying to figure out where you're supposed to go next, and as for the objectives, they don't make it 100% clear what you're supposed to do. I ended up depending on switching back and forth from walkthrough video to game, playing what I'd just seen. I don't like to depend upon walkthroughs/let's plays alot, I always try to play a game myself before watching it. But because I had no clue what to do here, I really needed them just to get where I did, and it's not even the end!Overall, Outlast is ""Ok"" maybe. But once you get past the scene with Richard Tragger, the game really wears off and becomes the same thing over and over again. It's not a hard game, yet it's frustrating. I enjoyed it at first, but after playing it for only a little while, it became boring, repeatative and each scene really lacked in difference. The first half is good, but after that, the developers really began running out of ideas, and just began to milk the same and same thing, over and over again, until the end, where they got it back a little. (Just to note, no I haven't got to the end, just seen it, also, I do not intend on playing this to the end, despite being close to it.)(UPDATE: I have now finished the game. Outlast is good, but I still stand by a majority of what I said in this review. The first half is good, but then it just gets repetative until the final scene with Billy Hope and the Walrider breathes new life into it.)"
