76561198099509764,Recommended,238320,9691506,"Posted: 31 March, 2014",all,-BigRed-,"I took my time and ""enjoyed"" this experience. I was very surprised to find that I finished in 11 hours. It felt far longer. I played about 2 hours per-sitting ... that was my ""sanity limit"". This is the first true survival-horror game I ever played.The ""Dead Space"" series (and all the zombie genre) is an example of a very different survival-horror theme, one where you have a means of defending yourself, of fighting back, even of ""winning"".Outlast has no such illusions. In this game, you get a palm-sized camcorder with a ""night view"" option, and that option really drains the battery. And a notepad, that you can't control, you make notes as dictated by the game. You have nothing else. You will be scrounging for batteries within the first hour.You're just a guy. A struggling reporter looking for your big break. You can run, you can jump, you can crawl, you can try to hide ... that's all you have, those are your only options.You'll quickly develope a fear of everything ... you'll encounter horror's that you aren't prepared to view ... visceral, bloody, ... real. I can honestly say that you'll wish you did not see some of the things that happen in this game ... You will jump in your seat, you will shout out-loud, your pulse will race, you will know true fear ...Everything that I've told you will happen ... to you ... and that is what makes this game so amazing.Note: I honestly feel this game should be rated Mature with an NC-17 label. Even 17 year-olds may be too young.I loved this game. I'm 51 years old and I ran ""like a school-girl"" with my heart racing ... actually cringing and leaning forward over the controls as if that would help me avoid being grabbed by what was chasing me.The first 90% of this game will force you to the edge ... the last 10% ... maybe.You must play in a darkened room. You must use the in-game gamma to give you true ""black"" darkness. You really need a good pair of headphones ... using speakers will scare the crap out of anyone in listening distance.Outlast is the first of it's kind and I fervently hope that more games will follow. See, us real people don't have amazing powers and an arsenal of deadly weapons ... we have courage and a need to uncover the truth ...Come face you fear ... and take another stepI rate this game a very solid 9.0 out of 10."
