,Recommended,238320,10118810,"Posted: 15 May, 2014",all,{<-DuRrP->} Riser the Bulwark,"Here's the deal with this game. Everyone wants more when it comes to video games, but in a survival-horror game you want quality over quantity and Outlast hits that nail. I bought it while it was on sale and was worth every penny (I can garuntee the length of the game is not worth the off-sale price). The game is short and can be beat in less than 10 hours, but the scares last a lifetime. When researching this game DO NOT form an opinion on how short it is (comes with S-H turf after all). The graphics are wonderful and the scares quite satisfying. Plot constantly twists and turn (like your head if caught sometimes XD) and the story is very in-depth and addictive. All in all, i give this game an 8.5 of 10 for scares alone. I do recommend this game be bought if it goes on sale again but wouldn't pay normal price for it."
