,Recommended,238320,24205891,"Posted: 9 July, 2016",all,Giraffe☤,"Outlast....... it's just as much as my heart could handle. I bought this game after it has been on the market for years. I watched youtube gameplays from pewdiepie a lot and should know where the game would take me to when i bought it. But still when I played the game, the thrill, the horror, the scares were still fresh, always fresh actually.I have never experienced such awesomeness in any horror game, not even close to ""not a lot"". For Red Barrels to actually make something new and revolutionary, it deserves a hundred percent positive review.Now for the start, the gameplay of this game is pretty simple. it's just run, hide, or die game. Simply no puzzle, no mini games in the game, not an open world but there are parts where you are in a maze and the game forces the pursuer to pursue You. Another challenge is, you have choices that you will make for yourself, you want to be paranoic and scared by every single person in the game, or be selective and brave, or be consumed by murderous curiousity. This is one of the first things that you will then feel throughout the game. Others might find the game a little funny, but for me, those guys might have problems, I personally consider this game a nightmare.However, this game has the charm that makes the player want to touch that shortcut to hell again and again, and again they meet hell. This curiousity that they trap you in, is something that you cannot avoid after you buy the game.After finishing the whole game (including the DLC). I found the enemies not scary anymore (their physical appearance) and the game does not give you nightmares in real life. It's just the tension you get when you dont want the bad guys to find and kill you, or get you when they chase you. This is the charm of the game. So don't be scared of buying it, or emptying your wallets. I really reccommend you to play this! Enjoy your nightmare!"
