76561198089003426,Recommended,238320,12293612,"Posted: 29 September, 2014",all,Cup O' Joe,"Outlast is a unique horror experience that most games don't offer. I played through the entire game before writing this review. I am a huge fan of the horror genre, and it is very hard to find a game that scares me. While this was an amazing game, it was not very scary. This may be different for other people, but there were probably about 10 jump scares, and there wasn't really any psychological horror in it. The game was atmospherically horrific however, because 75% of the game takes place in the dark. The enemies in it were decently scary, and what I enjoyed was that you can not fight back. I loved the graphics on this game, they had their own king of feel to them. The gameplay was okay, but it got very repetetive because you were constantly having to find two things while being hunted by an enemy. One of the cool things about the gameplay was the use of the camera, which has limited batteries and has a nightvision mode. Throughout the game you can find bonus documents and read about different psychopaths and such, which was a very cool collectible experience. The story in it was okay, it wasn't too story driven, but there was a story. The game is not at all like a Silent Hill, or any other game that just uses psychological horror. Difficulty wise, the game wasn't hard, however there were parts that I died in over and over. The game should take at least 6 hours to beat without a walkthrough, so it was decently long. Overall, Outlast is a great game to play and I highly reccomend it.8/10"
