76561198065183142,Recommended,238320,15237310,"Posted: 6 April, 2015",all,Blyatman,"Outlast is one of the scariest games I have ever played, and yes I would say it is scarier than Amnesia. The reason why it is effective is so obvious that I'm surprised more games don't do it. Here is the secret ladies and gentlemen. PACING. Yes, it truly boggles the mind, but PACING is the key to a good survival horror game. The game doesn't just start throwing you into an attack from a murderous zombie army with a shotgun in one hand and your♥♥♥♥♥♥in the other. You start reading about a strange facility, you travel there in your car, and enter it. Even after that you aren't attacked for about a half hour. Now, keep this in mind. The game does occasionally use jumpscares, but honestly I don't mind them. They are used sparingly and the scariest part is the anticipation of the jumpscare. They are only used about 3 times throughout the story. Now, I'm not going to spoil the story, so there won't be a breakdown on what I do and do not like about the story, but it is told fairly well through documents and notes found throughout the facility. Overall, I'd give the game about a 9/10."
