76561198175476175,Recommended,238320,24291096,"Posted: 13 July, 2016",all,Jashon2015,"It's an Amazing Horror game, Let me mind you I don't usually get scared easily but this game does mess with you mentally, It brings back what a Horror game truly is,It's not boring but it does get frusturating at times, Like I said this is an actual Horror game and I think that is very hard to pull off today with these wanna be Horror games Five nights at Freddies and ect, I believe that all Horror games should have these six elements, The 1st one is Disempowerment meaning you should engage agaist ememies and an eniorment that is stroger than you, They should take away your power and  I love how Outlast does that with the no combat system. Element number 2, You should feel isolated an example would be how you're trapped in a asylum and your main goal is to escape. Element number 3, It should have tension, Your character can't just go around being confident there has to be stress some sort of mental or emotoinal strain and Outlast does that by having your not only problem being trapped in an asylum but you having to deal with multiple enimies as you progress in the game.  Element number 4, A good Horror game should have uncertainty like you being unsure of what's gonna happen when you open a door. Element number 5, It should have a Lingering fear something to stay with you even after you stop playing or finish it, Like a scary movie about spiders would give you a fear of spiders after you watch it. Element number 6, An unbalaced, Imperfect, Relatable Protaganist, Meaning you should feel weak and fragile and only should have to rely on your smarts and Outlast again does that with the no combat system and where you either have to run or hide. Well to sum that all up Outlast is a damn good Horror game and game overall and you should try it maybe you'll like it maybe you won't but I garuntee it won't be a waist of time."
