,Recommended,238320,11293324,"Posted: 17 July, 2014",all,mahimahi,"This game truly packs their share of jumpscares throughout the game, and yes, it did manage to scare me often. The ambience is truly amazing and greatly fits and improves to horror scenes. And the soundtrack is good. ( In my opinion ) The game's conflicts however, seem to be a bit repetitive, usually requiring you to activate certain pumps/engines while avioding one of the games enemies who walks around looking for you. The game story overall is good, and has their share of plot twists.The graphics are highly detailed and realistic, matching the overall scene of Mount Massive Asylum very well. The asylum looks truly realistic, and I can't help being sucked into the game every once in a while.The only negative thing I would have to say about this game is its repetivity, like I recently stated, this game constantly requires you to keep activating engines and stuff, while evading the boss. You  can try rushing along, or you could use stealth, which involves alot of waiting for the right moment and eventually getting seen and running back.The game really fits as a survival horror, having only few ""fight"" scenes, one being when Dr.Trager last tries to kill you in the elevator.Overall, I would recommend this as a good horror game full of exciting ( and scary ) adventure.8/10If you're into horror games, go ahead and buy it, it's a good game to play."
