76561198080484234,Recommended,238320,10773048,"Posted: 24 June, 2014",all,kevski1969,"This is brilliant. I love the way that the in game video camera and it's night vision effects are so life-like. The graphics are very believable, while the brass stabbing music and sound effects add to the already tense atmosphere.I also like the way that you can hear the characters heartbeat and heavy breathing when he gets scared or runs for his life. Your character can also peep around the corners and look behind him while he is running. Very realistic indeed.This is NOT a monster mash up - In this game... You are trapped inside a world of hurt. All that you are armed with is a video camera with night vision capability, and the strong urge for self preservation. You have objectives to complete and no way of defending yourself.YOU... Are now the hunted. The only way to survive is to run for your life when you have to; creep about quietly sometimes, and also hide inside cabinets or underneath beds, and I find this approach extremely refreshing and very addictive.I’m a seasoned video game player of many years experience. I started off by playing on the arcade machines in the mid 1970’s, and have been hooked on video gaming ever since. I have grown up during the evolution of video games, and have bore witness to them evolving from arcade machines, to home consoles, to home pc's that todays younger generation now expect, demand, and also take for granted as soon as they learn to walk and stop burping breast milk!So - I have been around long enough to now expect extremely high standards in all of my video games today; and this one definitely does NOT disappoint. It is very believable and immersive to play.I give this game a very easy 9 out of 10.If you like this sort of stuff - What are you waiting for!!!Be warned though - This game is best played while you are all alone and in the dark, with headphones on while sitting on a BROWN towel.Most importantly of all – Outlast is so good; it’s not going to be one of those Steam games that you download and then shelf after a couple of hours play."
76561198060593306,Recommended,238320,10879023,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,Tickle Pants,Your name is Miles Upshur a reporter who has received an anonymous tip about some very disturbing things happening in Mount Massive Asylum. Armed with a camera and your ability to run fast you must investigate what has happened. What you will uncover is both shocking and terrifying. Outlast is probably one of the most frightening games I have ever played. The graphics are crisp and horrifying and the sound effects/sound track just add to the horror.This is one of these few indie games that come once in a while and throws caution to the wind trying to innovate upon a pretty dead genre. The fact that you have no weapons and you can only rely on your camera to see in dark further adds to the sense of impending doom that resonates in this game. There is never as sense that there is hope for Miles.I would recommend this game to anyone who loves story driven games. Outlast is not only pretty and scary it is actually a great story.9.5/10Ticklepants
