,Recommended,238320,8072809,"Posted: 16 December, 2013",all,Ruttis,"A first person survival horror game, heavily inspired by the genre defining horror title Amnesia: The Dark Descent, Outlast is arguably one of the scariest games out there.Much like in Amnesia, fighting off your enemies is out of the question. This means that you're left with no choice but to run or hide when encountered by one of the murderous inmates of the abandoned insane asylum. Within the first few minutes you'll be sneaking around the eerie dark corridors, watching your every step in fear of who, or what, might be lurking behind the next corner.Although loaded with a good amount of jump scares and somewhat predictable moments, Outlast manages to be a fun (not to mention scary) experience. If you're looking for a good horror game you should definitely consider buying it the next time you see it on sale."
