76561198048746314,Recommended,238320,10675386,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,NuclearFon,"I'm not one to get scared easily but Outlast is different from most other Horror games and movies. There is an incredible sense of atmosphere yielding moments of intense fear that last for quite some time, such that the only thing stopping you from closing the game out of fear is the chilling anticipation of what will come next and the deep need to survive the horrors that exist within the asylumOutlast offers a huge amount of gameplay that is almost doubled with the DLC Whistleblower. The story is gripping and shocking at the same time and is progressed through collectible documents and notes. The scares rely less on gore (although there is plenty) and more on atmosphere. Most horror games have a few good jump scares and that's it, Outlast is not like that. While there are several very good jump scares they are not the focus, they are just highlights, accents to the games creepy and horrifying narrative. The only downside to this game is that it has a somewhat cookie cutter style gameplay where you hit a button, hide from a monster and repeat. Nevertheless I would strongly recommend this game to anyone who likes to scare themselves silly. It also works great for group play because it is very fun to watch. 9/10."
