76561198072109352,Recommended,238320,9373458,"Posted: 7 March, 2014",all,N7_Infiltrator,"If you're interested in survival horror games, I'd highly suggest Outlast be on your game list. It's one of the best ones I've played in awhile (since Amnesia: TDD), and the story line is interesting enough to keep you playing. You have to use the environment and your intense parkour abilities, since you can't fight the enemies you face. You just have to either hide and hope they don't find you, or hope you can out run them.The only issues I can think of with this game is overall, it's not as scary as it's made out to be (a problem I've run into before with these kinds of games). There are jump-scares, and some of the enemies you face could make you uneasy, but it isn't one that I lost any sleep over. That, along with the continuous need to find batteries for the night vision function of your camera gets kind of tiring because it functions just fine without batteries. Your sight is just more limited and it isn't worth the hassle of finding the limited amount of batteries that spawn.Overall: 7.5/10"
