,Recommended,238320,7851198,"Posted: 30 November, 2013",all,Karudo | Mark,"Game : OutlastScore : 8/10Summary :Without spoiling the plot and or storyline i can tell you this game is amazing, do i dare to say it? yes, yes i will in my oppinion it surpasses the first Amnesia.Outlast is a very nice designed game where you as an journalist have to infiltrate an abbandoned mansion, or is it abbandoned? there is not a single moment in the game where you feel safe.... well maybe if you hide in a locker, but thats the only moment really! ;)The only ""weapon"" you have is a camera that has 2 modes, dark mode and a bit less dark mode... called nightvision among the people that know what they talk about.I highly suggest you buy this game if you are a fan of Horror/Tense/Suspension and jumpscares, trust me, if you play this game with your lights out, you will be afraid.I finished the game in rougly 7+ hours with friends at my side... yes i was to afraid to play it on my ownGood things about Outlast- The graphics are nice and it perfectly fits the entire atmosphere of the game- Its good that you can not carry a weapon around cause that will take away ALLOT of fun from this game- There are ALLOT of jumpscares in this game- The ending has a very nice plot-twist and it will screw with your brain a little.Bad- There are scripted events in the game, unfortunately you know when they happen taking away some of the fear.- The camera still works eventho its batteries are dead ( it works less tho )- The AI of the enemies are a bit meh, you can kite them in circles for minutes!All in all Outlast is an amazing addition to the Horror genre in the gaming industrie, it deserves a place next to Amnesia and the first couple Resident Evil-Please note this review is written on the base of my oppinion.Be sure to check out my other reviews!"
