76561198029555177,Recommended,238320,8314559,"Posted: 26 December, 2013",all,Mast3rHax0r,"The first thing that you propably wanna know about this game is this, are there♥♥♥♥♥♥♥in it? And I can gladly inform you that there are plenty...wait, you didn't wanna know that? Oh, well how about this, is the game scary? I can also answer yes to this question.The strongest part in the game is the atmosphere( what a twist right). Walking around the creepy Asylum can really be  spooky at times. 1 thing that improves the atmosphere is the camera, but I will talk about that more when I get to the gameplay part. Visually the game looks quite nice. The sound desing is great and even the soundtrack and voice acting are suprisingly good and creepy too. All these things combined create a truly creepy atmosphere.Now let's move on the the gameplay. First of all the camera. They really put that thing to good use. You will be spending most of the game using the cameras night vision mode, and when they take that away from, you feel even weak and vulnerable. Speaking of weak, there is no way to fight back in this game. If you see an enemy lurking around, you better hide( the whole hiding thing was also really well done) or run away as fast as you can.The makers of this game really nailed the 1st person view better than most games out there. The character movements seem realistic, and you never leave the 1st person view during the entire game. This can really draw you into the the game.Now to the bad stuff. I do think that the game has too many enemy encounters and the problem with this is that you start getting used to them towards the end, so they get far less scary. There are also quite a bit of jump scares, which do get kinda cheap a couple of times. The game is also a bit too short for my taste, I got through it in about 4+ hours. 1 thing that kinda bothered me(not sure if anybody shares my point of view on this but oh well) is that you don't die easily enough. You can survive multiple hits from enemies, which is something I don't like. It would have been more exciting if they took you out in 1 or 2 swings so you would have to be really careful all the time. But instead you can just tank dem hits.And last but not least, the story is nothing to write home about, and the last act of the game and the final ""twist"" are both quite weak.Overall, Outlast is an enjoyable yet terrifying experience, that all horror game fans should try out. It has it's problems, and because of the last 20-30 minutes, I had a really hard time giving it a score. But in the end, it still is 1 of the best horror games I have played in quite some time. With some minor tweaks, the sequel could be something truly special"
