,Recommended,238320,13755335,"Posted: 1 January, 2015",all,Gandhi,"Outlast is one of the best survival horror games I have ever played! The atmosphere is genuinely creepy, with great ambient effects to really draw out the effect on the player. I would recommend getting this game (maybe not the DLC). This game is also VERY graphic, so expect that if you plan to pick up this game. Guts and gore EVERYWHERE and there is some male nudity (minor in the main game and significant in the DLC).If I had to nitpick, I would say that the character models could have used some more detail as most of them aren't super detailed and the scarring looks a bit simple. That isn't to say that all the character models are this way, just the average ""patient"", if you will.The DLC is a big question when it comes to this game. I think the developers did a pretty ok job with it, but it uses many of the same elements (scare types, etc) as the main game. As the DLC is a prequel to the main game, I found that the main game lost some of its zing after playing the DLC. There are also some glitches in the DLC where two main baddies are spawned, a few of the jump scares are not exactly done super well, among a few other minor things. The DLC also has some really great things about it as the ""Gluskin"" enemy is pretty creepy I really really enjoyed how the story was filled out by playing the guy who originally leaked information to miles upshur (your character in the main game).In the end I highly recommend getting this game; however, it doesn't really have much replayability and the main game is about 2-2.5 hours in length. The DLC adds about an hour or so, which still ends up leaving the game pretty short. Ultimately, you are likely going to be playing this game once and then maybe whipping it out to scare your friends once in a blue moon. My advice is to pick it up while it's cheap, as it really is worth it."
