,Recommended,238320,31061147,Posted: 10 April,all,Jill van der Meer,"Greatest survival horror since the original Resident EvilsAs an avid horror game fan who's always craving for more, my expectations for Outlast weren't all too high - asylums, terrible secrets, yadda yadda yadda. Boring. Yawn. We've all seen it before. Actually, if it hadn't been for the 80 percent discount, I wouldn't have looked at Outlast twice. But I decided to give it a go.Boy, was I wrong.What Outlast loses in its boring premise, it gains back in gameplay. Run, hide, or die — love it! Not being able to fight back adds a whole new level of despair and horror ito the game. Knowing that the enemy could be lurking behind any corner at any time, and knowing that you have no way of defending yourself really makes the adrenaline kick in.The typical ""your flashlight might die"" -scheme has been replaced by the camrecorder — and it works. At times, I truly did feel like an investigating journalist trying to capture the horrors of an asylum. At times I was more worried about my camcorder batteries than I was about the patients trying to take my life. And, at times — if not most of the time — I felt scared. Just like a horror game should make you feel."
