,Recommended,238320,10674407,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,Chotato,"Game details:In Outlast you play as the Outlast. You play as Markcus Jerpons otherwise known as his callsign Dippus Chipper, a member of the Outlast group. The Outlast is a para-military group dedicated to wiping out all the paranormal activity in the world. You're sent on a suicide mission to Big Mountain Asylum in New Jersey after getting a tip (see Whistleblower DLC) about some zombie mutants that have taken over the asylum and taken your wife, Maryland Choe, hostage. It's your mission to use the advanced technology at your disposal to lead a team of Outlast specialists to find the infamous Doctor Richard and bring him to justice as well as finding your wife. You'll have to use your surroundings to your advantage if you want to survive. Trigger massive avalanches with C4, call in an AC130 gunship and more.Review:I really liked this game. It seemed like much more of a military simulation from the trailers than the actual game ended up being, which I believe ended in it's favor. I bought this game the day it came out and expected another ARMA clone, but was pleasently surprised. There was one mission I really enjoyed when your commanding officer Staff Sergent Charles Burkens climbs a radio tower while you defend from the milita and zombie army below. Normally I'm not a fan of protect missions but this was done very well and the explosive ending where you both go crashing down the roof of Big Mountain really surprised me.Conclusion:I really enjoyed this game and recommend it to anybody who likes a military shooter with minor spooks and ghouls."
