,Recommended,238320,19893584,"Posted: 23 December, 2015",all,coprolite,"Good tension and atmosphere.  You can't do much as the player except walk around slowly, and then run away quickly.  This limitation really forces you to listen and pay attention to the environment.  This is not a game for shooter fans.. there is no shooting.  Much of the game consists of moving from QTE to QTE, slowly.  The QTEs however are the best I've seen, requiring you to interact with the environment under stress, and resulting in many novel escapes and near-misses that make sense.  There are also some cool misdirections (things that seem scary but which aren't actually a threat).  Overall the environment is effectively enerving, which is probably great if you like horror stealth games.  I found some of the scariness softening overtime as it became clear that enemies path in a very mechanical repetitive way, but the uncomfortableness the game stirs up are undeniable.  I found myself not wanting to play because I wasn't in the mood for a tense experience, and ended up uninstalling before completing the game.  I still remember several moments from the game as if they happened yesterday, and that to me is saying something.  If you like games of this type, it is worth 5 bucks."
