,Recommended,238320,29552826,Posted: 28 January,all,Tuckyove,"This game is an instant classic of the survival horror genre, in my opinion. I picked it up for $5 during a sale and which I can honestly say was one of my most worthwhile purchases on Steam. At first I was too afraid to even open it, but after promising myself I'd play the first ten minutes just to say I tried, I was hooked. The gameplay is great, the scares are intense and the excellet blend of lighting and audio make it truly atmospheric. The story is masterfully written and in my experience, keeps you invested despite wanting to back out in fright. The camcorder being the sole usable tool is such an creative and innovative idea that I wouldn't be surprised to see used in other future titles. In addition, the DLC is a great continuation of the story that answers a few questions left at the end of the main game. If you're a fan of the genre, you're doing yourself a misdeed not playing Outlast."
