,Recommended,238320,21226206,"Posted: 15 February, 2016",all,Harley,"I'm a fan of games like Silent Hill, The Suffering, and Among the Sleep... Jumpscare games with tense anticipation.This game is scarier than anything I've played. Spent nearly 15 minutes real time sitting in the TV room with a bunch of the inmates staring at the blank screen of the television because I was too scared to roam the halls after a nasty encounter with one brute. The bad guys didn't bother me in there. I was tempted to stay.The immersion level of the game is amazing. The sounds and sights are cued so very well it's impossible not to get swept up in the nerve-wracking tension. In addtion to the expected ambient sounds of an old building riddled with who-knows-what monstrosities, the main character also makes noise. His camera makes noise. He breathes heavy when he runs or gets surprised by something. He makes noise when he bumps into things.The game jumps between normal vision, camera vision and night camera vision, dictating the visual experience you get. The night vision is especially creepy to me and very true to what I've seen on paranormal hunter reality shows. All very sense-convincing. Only thing that's missing is the smell of dust and fear-sweat in the air.Excellent game so far. Dunno if I'll finish it, it's so intense, but it was worth buying during the President's Day sale."
