,Recommended,238320,9762622,"Posted: 8 April, 2014",all,TomHorror,"If you are a fan of horror movies and/or scary games such as myself, then you will absolutely love this game. You will especially love this game if you like being scared in a game as there are countless moments in the game that will have your heart leaping out of your chest! The atmosphere in this game is horrifying and each scary moment is set up perfectly.The game also has a marvellous story, although first-time players may miss out on some story elements since they may not collect all of the documents scattered throughout the asylum, each of which will give the player more information on aspects such as some of the patients, the asylum staff, the asylum itself etc. However, the characters in this game more than make up for that as they are so terrifyingly memorable in that they will scare the living hell out of you (especially when you first play the game).Furthermore, the graphics in this game are phenomenal, especially for an indie game. The asylum almost seems real and the visuals give a raw and gritty look, and it definitely suits the atmosphere and story of the game. However, this game also contains a lot of gore as you go through the asylum since you'll be seeing a lot of blood pools and corpses throughout the game, as well as some gruesome death scenes, so if you don't like seeing blood and guts or gore in a game, then you may want to pass on this game as it contains a lot of gore as I said.The only other flaw I have with this game is that the ending felt somewhat anti-climactic, but I won't spoil it for you. Even then, the game is still very scary and lots of fun to play, especially when using headphones and having the lights turned off xDHowever, the developer (Red Barrels) have announced a new DLC (The Whistleblower) that could possibly fix the issue of the anti-climactic ending since it will ""actually stretch past the events of the first game to show the final chapter in Mount Massive 