,Recommended,238320,10047563,"Posted: 7 May, 2014",all,The_Reaper95,"This is honestly the only game in the Survival Horror genre that I have ever enjoyed.. Outlast has been criticised, Outlast has been praised.. Some people say that it isn't scary, some people are scared by it.. Fear is quite personal if you think about it.Firstly lets take a look at the history of Survival Horror to just prove a few people wrong about this game. The original Survival Horror, or rather the first game to be defined with this genre; Resident Evil for the Playstation, is that game scary to you? Because it isn't to me, yet that is the game that made the genre, so why do we forget that? Then criticise this game or other games as to how they are not true Survival Horror.Let me tell you about what, to me personally, a Survival Horror game is.. The fear of subtelty, knowing that somewhere out there someone is stalking you, the andrenaline you feel when you are being chased, the fear of being found when you are hiding, there is no guarantee of you being safe, and no guarantee you are in danger... But your main goal is to Survive, to push through each area of the game and survive, get through the story, take in the information from your surroundings alone, set an atmosphere for you to actually feel emotions from, that to me is what a Survival Horror game is. And Outlast delivers on that.(I have heard other people say similar things about Resident Evil 1 funnily enough)Now I have played through this game, more than once, however I got it originally on a different platorm, I played it on the PS4 when it came out for free in February for PS Plus (A service that gives free games monthly on all platforms which include PS4, PS3 and PS Vita) I enjoyed it immensely, I had seen gameplay of the game from various YouTuber's and I didn't actually enjoy watching it that much to be honest, but playing the game I thought ""I'll give it a go, after all, IT'S FREE!"" and as I said, I enjoyed it immensely. The game was just so incredible for me considering I have never liked a Survival Horror game before, so you can imagine my surprise as to how good it was to me, also I'm not easily impressed might I just add, the game set a creepy atmosphere, yet because of my intrigue about the game, I press forward, I get through the game, I love it, I play it another 3 times on higher difficulties, try and get all the files, fail, but stil enjoy it. Every section of the game to me is perfectly timed, from the introduction to the mechanics to introduction of each psychopathic character that stalks you throughout Mount Massive Asylum, the area's, lore, even the music.Let me talk about the characters for a while shall I?Firstly, I would like to go through the characters in a random order, rather than the order you encounter them, that way it doesn't truly spoil it if someone reading this review (Who am I kidding?) decides to buy and play the game with my review in mind. (Again..)Right, Father Martin, he's an interesting supporting character to me, he sets the mood at certain intervals, gives you a sense of direction even, he never truly interferes, never truly guides you, but he gives you informaiton, tells you things, drops you hints when you see him, that sort of thing..The Twins.. This creepy rapey looking pair stalk you at times with Machetes... They are also Naked so that adds to the creep factor.. Two guys (Brothers mind you) following you around, butt naked, with blades.. Yeah. Creepy as ♥♥♥♥.The Doctor.. What can I say about this psycho?! He is ♥♥♥♥ing insane, thinks he's helping people almost, tries to get to know you before he kills you, he acts jokey about the fact he's chasing you as well, I enjoy his one liners when he loses track of you I can tell you muchChris Walker... Now he is, by far, the most enjoyable character in the story for, me, he follows you throughout the whole game, and you almost enjoy it, I would love to know who his Voice actor is (I really should have looked it up before now, but I will after this!) because his lines are just great. The feeling of knowing when he specifically is stalking you, and it's better when on Harder difficulties because you'll die in one hit from him, a large brute of beast, he stalks you, muttering away to himself.I love the atmosphere he creates simply by being there, my immense joy for having experienced this character in Outlast is one of my main motivations to have bought this game again on PC and of course picking up the DLC whilst I was at it. I also went ahead and got all the Trading Cards for this game, crafted the badge and got a Chris Walker emoticon.. I did all of that, just for Chris Walker, I love this game and I would reccomend it to anyone.. They should make some Outlast ringtones XD, especially if the voice actor for Chris Walker makes one :P ""LITTLE PIG I HEAR YOUR PHONE RINGING, YOU CAN'T HIDE NOW""Buy this game people, I would talk about the DLC but I won't right now, (Which is goddamn incredible too!) So please people, don't judge this game, for me it was incredible, I can't make others like it but I can at least say, don't bloody judge it.. Enjoy Outlast!"
