,Recommended,238320,31795835,Posted: 16 May,all,Valerius,"Outlast is supposed to be one of the scariest game of the last few years...And it is. Kinda.You play as Miles Upshur, a journalist that has come to investigate an asylum after receiving an email, pretending that strange things are happening in said asylum.And so you are armed with nothing else than a camera (brand not specified), allowing you to 'see' in the dark with an infrared feature that sucks batteries faster than a succubus can suck your soul.And thus, with your camera you bravely dodge, hide, run for your life and overall try not to die horribly in that asylum !You meet many enemies, well, two kinds of enemies that is ; the basic goon, armed with an axe, a wood plank or any other homemade weapon and what I call 'bosses'. They aren't much more dangerous that the basic goons...oh wait, yeah they are. They can kill you instantly !Suffice to say that you avoid any and all enemies in this game, and at some point I thought it was more annoying than scary !Talking about scary...The game is not very scary, basically good old fashioned jump scares that never failed to make me jump a bit (yeah I'm sensitive to those), but I would say that if you remove all of those you remove every scary element of the game.The ambience is well made, but not so oppressing, at least it didn't affect me the way I imagined it would :oBut there is one element, one thing that happens in the game that really disappointed me...I won't be too specific about it, to avoid any spoilers, but I will just say that it felt like a scenaristic laziness. The guys that made this game just had to use that overused, overrated, crappy plot twist that has never worked, and never will, and it's a damn shame...I shall now summarise my experience with this game :Pros :- The devs kept their concept to the end- Good feeling about it all- Very stressful situations- Basic but efficient gameplayCons :- Lazy plot twist that kinda killed it at the end- Overused situations (get the key to open the door...)- A bit frustrating sometimesOverall it is a good game, a very good game to some extent, but it could have been a great game if not for that plot twist at the end...I recommend it nonetheless !PS : The DLC Whistleblower is basically the same as the main game, so the review stands for it also :)My commented playthrough :https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLffYB9tYe2fzPb2z9ByvqfdoQLHM2e30r"
