,Recommended,238320,8791577,"Posted: 20 January, 2014",all,SuperBandicoot64,"Outlast follows the horrifying tale of investigator Miles Upshur, as he ventures into the once abandoned Mount Massive Asylum to uncover its dark secrets, while being pursued by the horrifying figures that once and still lurk there. The best way to describe Outlast is a modern day Amnesia: The Dark Descent. You spend the game exploring the dark environments while running and hiding from phsycopaths galore.THE GOODOutlast is good in many departments, but the place it shines the most is the presentation. Outlast is one of the best looking games  I have seen. Even if you were to put it on the lowest settings, the game still looks amazing. While it is not the best looking game ever, It is one of the best looking games I have seen. Another great thing is something that is vital to make your game scary: the characters and environment. Whether your being pursued by the intimidating yet interesting Chris Walker, or the disturbing and absolutely insane doctor, you be constantly on your feet for the majority of the game. (Keyword being ""Majority"") Another place the game shines is it unique camera system, Which gives it a found footage vibe. While you can explore the game without barely using the camera, you need it for two things: you need it to learn a bit more about the story, As the Protagonist will at times make a comment about the situation at hand in the form of notes. Its also used to get around areas with its night vison camera, which is vital to getting around in the game.THE BADWhile there is more good than bad, there many problems with the game. One of these problems are the length of the game. The game (depending on how good you are) took me and others about 5 hours to complete. This is by far the second worst problem with the game. Another problem is the final boss. While most enemy's in the game are memorable and well designed, the final boss is as bland as they come. I do not want to spoil anything, but you will know exactly what im talking about. Finally, the worst part about Outlast is the 3rd act. To me, the game at that point became very repetitive, and just not scary. And to top it all off, we get a ending that's complete s@#t.VERDICTOverall, Outlast is a very decent game and you should defiantly buy it: During a sale.SCORE:6.5/10I also apologize for some of my poor grammar in this review :)"
