76561197966468803,Recommended,238320,29629406,Posted: 1 February,all,Momentum,"Ok, so... I don't really remember writing a review for a Horror-game before, and I'm sure that, somewhere out there, are a bunch of adrenaline junkies hollering at me: ""YOU CALL THIS A HORROR-GAME?"" Yup. Damned Straight. No, it's not Resident Evil, or Doom 3, or Evil Within, Left 4 Dead Part (insert number here) or whatver else you base your thrills on. It's a walking simulator, I noticed... You don't GET an arsenal of weapons to kill all MF'ers. You get a camera with an infrared function, a journal you don't even have to write or read, you get dropped of at the front door of creepy asylum that looks big, but IS HUGE, you find your way inside, and AWAY WE GO!I'll try and be careful with spoilers here.Dark rooms and halls, flickering lights, plot scares that not only work, but actually managed to scare me AGAIN 2nd playthrough, even though I knew it was coming. And then there's the ""nice"" people you meet; the patients and staff of this fine facility are not only scary, they are down right DISTURBING! You can't fight them (nor should you... You're a skinny, white reporter with a notebook, a camera and a probably a name tag that says ""little pig"" or something.) You RUN from the big bad wolves. You HIDE! And even when you do, you still have to be smart about it, 'cause they're LOOKING for you! And they WILL find you!And then, of course, there's how the story develops... - Like a horror game/walking simulator SHOULD! - Running, panting, heart-in-your-throat, out of one hopeless situation into another. Running away from some VERY bad people, WHO DEFINITELY don't have your best interests at heart, right into the waiting arms of somebody WAY worse!!! And, (even if you don't even take the time to read the story or the journal along the way,) there are still some gutwrenching, tongue-biting, crap-your-pants twists in the plot that'll have you thinking twice about playing the game by yourself.Controls: Not perfect. But they aren't hard to learn or master. And while you will make mistakes with them, they're more likely be because your under stress and don't get the controls right, rather than the controls glitching out on you.Graphics: Gruesome. In the good way. It's juuuust simple enough that you won't fry your computer unless you actually TRY, but juuuust detailed enough that you'll probably wish it wasn't.Story: Brutal, Disturbing, Suprising and VERY Creepy, obviously. Tip for 1st playthrough: whenever you think you've seen the worst scare this game has to offer, you can be damned sure you're wrong, and you will find out. (Whistleblower adds even more.)Overall: For a walking simulator horror-game, this game sets the bar. 10/10 (And the sequel's cooking as we speak, so they just might jump over it, grab it, and beat us all scared stiff with it.)Ok. I'll hand out the big compliment the more twisted of the dev's probably want: ""WARNING! DO NOT PLAY THIS GAME IF YOU HAVE A HEART CONDITION!"" I'm no medical authority, but I'd feel bad if I didn't warn you..."
