76561197976515781,Recommended,238320,22210229,"Posted: 2 April, 2016",all,fishhooks,"Let me start out by saying that I am not a fan of Horror-Survival games.  This review is posted for those of like mind.  I don't play video games to act as I would in real life...I play to do amazing things.  I play Total War because in real life, I'll never command a massive army and build an empire.  I play Fallout and Metro because I'll never actually live in a post apocolyptic world where amassing weapons and slaughtering bandits is the means to my survival.  And I don't usually play Horror-Survival, because in real life...I'd run away and hide from these threats.  So I don't want to do that in my gaming.Having said that...many die-hard fans of the genre may disagree with my review, and that's ok...I would not dare to challenge the assessment of more experienced players in this space.  Personally, I didn't think the game was ""scary"",  but that's a pretty subjective term.  What one person finds frightening, another may laugh at.  So I'll just say that I found the game to be an awesome excersize in stealth.Regardless of what anyone may think about the 'horror' aspects of the game, it boils down to the ability to effectively sneak past adversaries, gather intel or items, and get out without being detected.  And the tension and anxiety that accompanies those efforts is delightfully intense.Bottom line, I enjoyed the game start to finish.  Die-harders may take issue with my comments, and as I said, I won't take exception to the opinions of more experienced horror-survival players.  But for those of you who are NOT fans of the genre, I would suggest you pick this one up.  If nothing else, it's a good way to expand your horizons.P.S.  Just finished the dlc, Whistleblower, and it contains the most disturbing scenario I've seen in 20+ years of gaming."
