,Recommended,238320,18942639,"Posted: 7 November, 2015",all,Anna Banana,"Outlast is a truely horrific experience.  From the very beginning, the warped atmosphere will leave you looking over your shoulder.UPDATE:  I've now played Whistleblower, and my opinion hasn't really changed towards the main game.  See my whistleblower review for my thoughts on it.Pros:-The story is interesting.  However, it honestly isn't interestingenoughto make you really care.  (See this continued in cons).  I think this is because the game is more focused on gameplay.-Night Vision Camera!  It's a cool take on the light-giving tool mechanic.-The environment made me feel genuinely scared at points-Less Jumpscares, more Psychological Horror-You can look down and see your whole body! (Great attention to detail from the developers).Cons:-By the end of the game the story is, without spoiling anything, open to interpretation, I felt confused and wanted to know more.  Perhaps that's just me, but I think it could've been better.-The game does at times feel like a rendition of Amnesia: The Dark Descent, with more annoying enemies.  In Amnesia, Enemies tend to permanently disappear after an encounter, not roam.  In Outlast, they roam.  This may be a pro to some and a con to others, but I mention it in my cons list because after a few times the game felt like hide and seek in the dark.-The hide and seek parts make completing objectives while tip toeing around enemies annoying rather than scary or adrenaline-fueled.  Because of this, the game took me over a year to actually get around to finishing (I started August 11th, 2014 and finished November 7th, 2015), mainly due to being annoyed that after making so little progress, I had to stop and play hide and seek again.-A very interesting type of enemy that could have been a nice addition to the overall game only appears at the end, which was disappointing.I always try to list around the same amount of Pros and Cons, so don't take my opinion as too negative.  Outlast is definitely something worth playing if you're interested in the Horror Genre.  8/10 from me."
,Recommended,238320,1460163,"Posted: 7 September, 2013",all,J o n e x,"For the first time in a long time, I was properly scared while playing a game!Atmosphere is everything in Outlast. The sound design is superb, with little sounds indicating the presence of nearby enemies and tense ambient music when something significant happens in the game world. The attention to detail is another factor that creates such an effective atmosphere. The walls look real, lighting has a full spectrum of dark to light, and animations are realistic.The camera is a nice gameplay element. The night vision is the most realistic I’ve seen in games and extremely creepy when navigating pitch black environments (plenty of those).What I enjoyed most about Outlast was the disturbing story. I won’t spoil anything, but it’s very well done and there are certain moments that really shine. The only problem was how quickly it finished and left me wanting more.Buy this game. It’s short, but very well made.♥♥♥♥ THE SEWER PART."
