,Recommended,238320,23504605,"Posted: 11 June, 2016",all,Baldwin Don Titskannone III,"Reasons to play this game:1. You can see your own♥♥♥♥♥♥in the DLC10/10 would wack again!No OK for real now. Reminder tho: this is more like a personal experience than a decent review. I start with an unimportant intro, followed by a complete ♥♥♥♥♥torm of words about my own experience with the game, but at the end I sum up some pros and cons. So if you’re not really into reading a lot of unimportant but straight-out-of-the-heart commentary, you can directly scroll down to the summary.I bought Outlast during the Steam sales last October (Halloween and stuff) and I was so excited to play the game, just because of the trailer. So when I finally jumped into it - together with a friend sitting next to me ofc - I was very excited and curious. Sadly, after the 2nd jump scare (no spoilers, there is more than one jump scare in the game) my friend and I screamed like two little ♥♥♥♥♥es and I turned off the game, without playing it for a couple of months.After a few months, I restarted, accompanied with two more friends, hoping we would outlast a bit longer, but now I got stuck in the 1st ""hide mission"", you know, those objectives when you need to sneak around without getting detected or else your head will be ripped off.. So yeah, I had a bad start playing this game. BUT: one summer day, in my attic during a great storm, I finally found the man - or woman, no sexist here - in myself and completed Outlast in just a few hours.The thing I loved the most about Outlast was its ambience. Sure, there are a bunch of jump scares and all that, but what made the horror in this piece of art was for me everything else: the environment, the music, the NPC's, but let’s start with the gameplay. I got used to playing “the vulnerable victim who can't fight back""-thing, since I played Slender and Amnesia and all that, but this game took it to a whole new level. First of all: THE ♥♥♥♥ING HANDCAMERA! It's such an amazing idea, and was executed very well. (NOTE: remember to put on your camera after a cut scene, because sometimes that doesn't happen automatically and then you forget recording and the game won't add notes to your journal.) Second: the parkour. Although sometimes a bit unrealistic (""Oh no, I'm followed by murderers, let me just wrench myself between these racks and they'll stop following me"") it was really amazing to know that you have a force - your agility - to outsmart your pursuers. Technically, it also worked very smoothly. I don't have a gaming laptop, so I couldn't play it on high settings - which I recommend, ambient feeling, y'know - but it almost never lagged or glitched or whatever. As said, the true horror of Outlast isn't in the jump scares, but in things like the environment. I remember myself thinking ""Oh really, an asylum? How original"", but boy oh boy original it was.!!!MINOR SPOILER ALERT!!!Although it all started very cliché, with the crazy people and stuff, you'll learn after a while that there is something MORE to it, and with more I mean supernatural... That's what I actually kinda disliked about the game, since I am not a big fan of supernatural stuffENDING OF SPOILER ALERTBut then again, how amazing is a game when you get to love it, even though you're not a fan of the storyline?I also deeply recommend playing The Whistleblower DLC since it gives a lot more information about the storyline, which is a bit unclear after completing the normal game.To sum up (for all the lazy people who did not read my interesting opinion)PRO:- the gameplay (camera, parkour, hide and sneak)- the music- the NPC's (they are REALLY ♥♥♥♥ed up, I can tell you that. They are also very memorable. There won’t pass a day without you thinking about Chris Walker, Trager, Wernicke and – ofc – Eddie “The Groom” Gluskin. They were given so much personality! )- the ambience and environment (especially the truly disgusting parts, they make Outlast Outlast)CON:- the unrealistic aspect of pursuers stopping to pursue you after you wrench yourself between racks- the story (my humble opinion, one of the main aspects of the story is something I don't like)- THE MOANING!!! For real, let me explain this quickly. Although it adds a lot of tension, hearing your character moan and his breath trembling, it got kind of annoying after a few hours. On the bright side, the game doesn't take more than a few hours, so that's fine.I can't wait for Outlast 2 hihi #shamelessfanboy"
