,Recommended,238320,17851524,"Posted: 2 September, 2015",all,FinDefaulted,"Tiny spoiler alert.Kind of like Amnesia. You navigate through a dark and scary asylum. Gameplay is rather interesting and there were lots of times that I got jump scared, but the overall ""Oh♥♥♥♥♥♥ oh♥♥♥♥♥♥quot; feeling disappears quite fast.This is a rather short game and to increase the gameplay time, there are ""puzzles"" in which you need to ""get x items""or ""open/close x stuff"". I don't really see the point in forcing the player to avoid some big bad guy while trying to find/use something to advance. It was kind of thrilling the first time when you escape the fat guy and end up avoiding one mainiac to turn on the valves, but after that it starts to feel annoying, since it feels forced and breaks the flow of the game.[SPOILING A LOT HERE]Then there is the super mega ghost, walrider. I kind of feel like they got inspired by F.E.A.R. but I think the game would have been more enjoyable with just the crazy maniacs.In the end outlast was a good horror game and you'll propably like it, but I wouldn't call it the scariest game ever."
