,Recommended,238320,31619168,Posted: 7 May,all,agriba,"Hide and Seek the game.Outlast is a fast paced horror game where the character can't fight back so he must either run or hide.Sneaking into an insane assylum where the nuts have taken over, you have to survive the blood soaked horror house and its inmates.  The gameplay is simple but the variety of enviroments and enemies make for enough variety to keep things interesting.  As well, there is an added weight to the game as story events that hurt your character can be felt as you play which really adds a sense of danger.Outlast really is over the top in blood and guts, and it does those things better than actual horror.  That isn't to say the game isn't scary, but if you are only looking for scary there are better games.  Outlast gives a nice mix of fast pace, horror, and intensity as it tries to be as disturbing as possible.It's a solid game.  Not huge.  Not a lot of replay value.  But the first go of it is quite memorable.  I'd recommend it to horror fans.  Maybe not as much as some other games such as Amnesia which is much scarier, but I'd still recommend it."
