,Recommended,238320,23135606,"Posted: 22 May, 2016",all,Dalek:.,"Outlast is a fantastic horror game, which had me on the edge with tension from pretty much start to finish. You're visiting this mental asylum (a very big one I should add) which is full of secrets and is sealed off from the outside world with no internet, and no phone signal. You're a journalist that has gone to investigate what it's all about.You have no weapons, and are only equipped with a video camera to gather evidence and use it as nightvision. Unfortunately however your camera seems to be one past its expiry date with batteries that leak faster than the BP oil spill, so you have to be careful as to when you want to see in the dark at various points in the game.That's all there is to it really, it's quite scary and definitely well worth playing if you want to have a challenge of getting through a horror game. In some ways the game reminds me of Penumbra, which is also another great survival horror game series I recommend. However, there are a whole lot less puzzles in comparison in this game."
