,Recommended,238320,9011773,"Posted: 7 February, 2014",all,that's what she said,"The game of many logic faults and impressive yet outdated a bit visuals.May well worth your time, even be revelation. Or may not.My guess is that more casual horror-fans will enjoy it more. So if you like Amnesia or something that modern and don't know what the hell was Clock tower, Forbidden siren, and Silent Hill is just a s**ty movie for you - then you'll enjoy it. If you want something really scary and psychological (because monsters within us are a lot scarier) - pass, you'll get bored to death.Yeap, players don't lie - Outlast looks good, performs well and cam effects are pulled out right. Sounds are great. Yeap, seems like a good start. But it's not.Horror aspect maybe will scare 14yo girl, but it's actually nothing in comparison to any horror game from the past. It's just another 'run-like-♥♥♥♥♥' game without any believable logic in it. Sadly sometimes game has it's moments when you are like 'omg jesus' ('you like watching, don't you?'). But then it goes back to 'run from the guy' and finger-cutting-scene or something else uninspired. And it goes worse and worse till the very end when it gets borderline dumb.You can stand some serious beating, but you can't fight back. Because... it's gamedesigner desicion. Yeah, grown up guy that runs like hell from some lunatic and hides under the bed. Yeah, really?Your cam eats batteries for breakfast. And dinner. It drinks them like russians drink vodka. So you'll be pants down in the dark in no time. Maybe it was intended to encourage me to use night vision less, but it was bad decision in the first place.Actual gameplay is a mix between 'do what gamedesigner says' and stealth. Somewhat stealth, because there is no proper stealth. I must admit first encounter was tense, but it wears off in that same encounter. *turn Benny Hill theme, you'll get that kind of running*. And next time you'll be turning valves/pushing some buttons again.For some reason Asylum feels absolutely sterile cardboard cutout for game's mechanics. There is nothing to explore, there is no believable layout, there is nothing at all in it. It feels like it was made around the player to the point when you can actually imagine how director says 'cut' and character shake hands with some psycho and they go to get a drink. It is that sterile and synthetic. And definitely will not add to experience to anyone who are into story games (story is pretty predictable and poor written), who wants to study game's lore (there is none, don't look for it), who wants absolute immersion (there is nothing to immerse in - it's just body-horror hollywood-style rollercoaster ride). And that terrible secret mentioned on store page... is laughable. I mean it, scenario goes brain-dead at some point, don't dig into it.So in conclusion - don't take this game for more than it is and you'll be fine. People say it's a horror miracle. No, you'll be disappointed. It's a decent game, but there is nothing new and nothing really amazing. Just your weekend slasher movie. Bring some beer."
