76561197984359324,Not Recommended,238320,29084832,Posted: 7 January,all,jgfoto,"Outlast is  a shock scare game. The start of the game is quite tense but after playing for about 2 hours I found the recipe very basic....try not to  be seen or if you are, either run or hide(there is usually a bed or cupboard somewhere near by).The scariness soon wore off. Not being able to fight back is fine by me...lets face it...in a real world scenario the majority of people would leggit when confronted by spooky looking insane killers.Not being able to throw an object to distract or confuse the fruitcakes is out of order.There isn´t an awful lot to do in this game in the form of problem solving, most of the time you have to wander onwards with a few minor hurdles  along the way.Thankfully I bought this while it was only 4,99...if I´d have paid more I would have been disappointed.I´m the kind of person who likes to explore a game to the fullest, in saying that...I managed to complete it after 10 hours.I didn´t even know that I´d come to the end of the game when suddenly the end credits were rolling...hmm.This game is alright but definately not as scary as it´s been hyped up to be.I don´t think I´d recommend this game because it hasn´t really achieved anything more than Doom did years ago.For 4,99 try it out...maybe I´ve played too many scary games to feel that this had something the others didn´t.Best summed up... Atmospher is good. Graphics are dated. Weak story. Nearly No dialogue. Hardly any interaction with surroundings."
