76561198080825372,Not Recommended,238320,24450195,"Posted: 21 July, 2016",all,Gremlin448,"Run, Hide and Get Scared & Run. Hide and Hide Some More DLCOutlast is indeed a visually appealing game with decent sound effects, lighting and design however it’s not enough to veil the many its many flaws.  As anyone knows horror, it’s a very hard medium to get right and this game didn’t go all the way for me in terms of what makes horror so fascinating.  Sure it contains violence, nudity and profanity like a typical horror movie, but what’s lacking is the originality, the risks in playing with taboos subjects, connecting with the protagonist(s) and see how far they’re willing to go make it to the end.  I’ve played this game four times (twice for the main game and twice for the DLC) to filly analyze the game, collect all the goodies and fully immerse myself into it to the point that I can even talk about it.  That being said, the game suffers from repetitious puzzles that utilizes little to no thought at all, the AI is extremely predictable and stupid to the point where once you understand how they’re program, they come less threatening, and wish I knew more about the characters I’m playing I can remotely care for them or even allow them to make choices that’ll change the outcome of the story.Overall, the game feels incomplete and truly wished they step it up in their upcoming game and take risks.  Even though I may have selected not recommend, I actually wanted to select both because people have to play this game to really know why I critique it the way I do because of its setting. Also while playing the game I felt like I was riding an intricate escalator with twists, turns, ascend, descend, go backwards and forwards, but ultimately it’s just one path I’m forced to ride on with a few stops on the way to the end or what others say a “walking simulator” with jump scares like some small time fair ride.  Anyways, the lists below are my thoughts on the game, so I hope they’re helpful and illuminate why I think this game is holding back.  Here they are:Both characters in the game aren’t interesting enough to empathize with (maybe Waylon because he’s married with two kids and that’s motivation enough to survive for him, but there’s virtually no introspective with him or Miles in regards to their situation or a dark side)Speaking of Miles, we really don’t know much about him other than his occupation and wants to get his hands on a juicy story, but that’s it.  It’s either reactions from his notes or hearing him breath heavy when hiding from malnourished psychos, Chris Walker and Rick Trager.  Billy is the only one the player can’t hide from.Speaking of the Camcorder, why couldn’t we use it as a puzzle element to allow to player to record stuff and then play it back for helping out for clues or anything?  The camcorder’s two functions are recording and night vision.  Can’t rewind or fast forward for whatever reason on it either.Using Asylums in horror genres been done to death and wished the game was more creative in its approach. I also wished that what we do in Mount Massive have an effect where the game changes depending the choices we made rather or not they were good or bad outcomes since horror loves the unexpected and the unknown.I’m fine with having no weapons or being combat focused, but wish I had the option to defend myself with the use of tools or use my surroundings to stun my foes, potentially kill them or have them trapped with clever puzzle solving elements and making player think outside of the box.All I can hope for is that the sequel to step up its game and take risks.In many ways, I’m glad the game exists and will give credit to credits is due for its visuals, sound effects and the character models.  That being said, why didn’t Miles’s finger suddenly stop bleeding after Rick cut two of them?  Wouldn’t it be a good objective to find bandages to not only stop the bleeding, but also to prevent Rick from finding Miles easier from the blood trail which make hiding not an option?While playing this game, I felt that there was some turf war going on and Miles was reluctant to be a part of Father Martin’s team by appointing Miles to be his “witness” and when to all that trouble to drug you and place Miles into his cell in the prison ward where he seems to have control over.  If that’s the case, then why are his “lambs” trying to kill him?  Chris I understand since he’s a free agent along with Billy, Rick is in charge of the medical ward, so that his turf, but wouldn’t make sense for Miles to interview these crazies since he’s on Martin’s team.  When you get to the administration again in the game, you’ll see what I’m talking about and wonder why were they’re trying to kill Miles in the first place.Again so much they can do with this game, but unfortunately from other critics of this game, it does feel like a walking horror simulator where what the player does has no real effect at all, see this jump scare and that jump scare and then do some filer to make the game longer.Regardless of my critique, try it out for the first time and then if anyone have the patience, play it again to see  why others are being so critical about the game."
