,Recommended,238320,10648996,"Posted: 21 June, 2014",all,hexaflexagon,"I'm not even finished with this game yet, but it's killing me. Unfortunately my computer is laggy and the graphics aren't as great as they would be due to that. I repeatedly run into things, can't move due to lag, and end up dying.But anyhow, it's a great horror game, although I scare easily. The music's really nicely done. It creates anticipation, atmosphere and anxiety. While there are the cliché jump scares, setting, and artwork for rooms, it's still a very chilling game. Gore, blood everywhere, fire, darkness, chase scenes, corpses everywhere are all cliché scares and we all know it. But the fact that you don't exactly know where to go and do makes it scary. It's unpredictable and twists and turns are everywhere throughout the game. (Quite literally.) When you have to use the night vision on your camera, it's super creepy. You don't know when the darkness will go away and you don't want to use up batteries. You don't know when the next battery will show up.Although the repetitive tasks are a bit annoying. (Pull levers, drain water, etc.) And at those points the game isn't really even scary and the enemies just become immensely annoying. And when you're not playing on insane difficulty, you would prefer to die and start over at the checkpoint rather than continue from your current place.But so far, this game is really interesting and keeps on making me want to play. But I don't ever play it if I'm alone, to be honest."
