,Recommended,238320,16571847,"Posted: 20 June, 2015",all,ElevenMink3,"This is a must have for horror fans and has an excellent scares and chase scenes. The story is okay, and is pretty straight-forward. The game gets a little repetitive with the predators, because the only thing you can do is hide, and if your presence is already known, you can only run into a room, close the door behind you, and THEN hide. But don't get me wrong: I DO really love this game and the bad guys make me scream every time!The main storyline is that you are Miles Upshur, an  investigative-reporter who plans to sneak/trespass inside Mount Massive Asylum with his trusty camcorder to film some illegal goings-on that was brought to his attention by an anonymous email sent by someone working within the prison. Then you notice blood and such on the walls, the big menacing gates close behind you, and then you realize that the murderous and deranged inmates escaped, and you feel a strange need to escape!The game really puts the ""jump"" in ""jumpscare"", but it only has, like, TWO or THREE in the whole game, and it gets you when you forget about the last one. It isn't known for jumpscares is the thing, but the game is startling throughout the entire experience.The intense gore and vulgarness is what makes the game unsettling, as you come acrossblood and intestines splattered all over walls, watch in terror as many people are slaughtered, get two of your fingers cut off by an insaniac with huge scissors, and I've even seen somebody ♥♥♥♥ a dead body.Yes, quite disturbing.As for the Whistleblower DLC (DownLoadable Content) it is just probably just 1 hour short of gametime as the original, and is much more disturbing/discusting,as you come across two more sensative topics: cannibalsm and polagamy. Yes, you do come across a person eating another fellow person, who even stuffed the other guy's head in an open microwave and promptly digs into him and eats his stomach. Then there is a deranged guy who gives surgery on men and... let's just say... he does his best to give sex changes. He tries to turn men into women so that he can raise a family with them. It is very inhumane and sick stuff.It's pretty traumatizing... I may never sleep again...The main storyline of Whistleblower is that YOU are the guy who sent the email in Outlast to Miles to tell him about the illegal stuff that's happening in the asylm and then your boss realizes you are a traitor, so he deals with you in a manner that would spoil too much of the story. Actually I'm just too lazy to explain it and put spoiler text over it.Since Whistleblower is just Outlast from a different perspective, there isn't mush else I can say about it. They are both good games, but pleeeeeease don't play if you are 11. I've made that mistake.so 9/10 wud pervertedly watch corpse get f*cked agin"
