,Recommended,238320,11467731,"Posted: 29 July, 2014",all,Melon,"Personal Rating: ""Worth playing""Traditional Rating: 10/10Genre: Survival HorrorI originally bought Outlast from the Steam Summer Sale 2014 for £4 and it was the best purchase of the year! This game brings hype in every part of the game and the jumpscares are really well planned.  Then comes the story.The games takes place in a Blood Thursty Asylum, you take control of Miles Upsher, a Journalist trying to get a story worth printing. But is it easier than he thought?As for the comparison of Amnesia, it has the same game mechanics apart from the fact that you can vault over objects inbetween running from the most fearful characters of gaming. You will find that you will be running to save you're life and continue the story!On a scariness level -Outlast suceeds as for being a good comparison to Amnesia. The lighting in different parts of the game gives you a more horror feeling and a more realistic thought as you continue. The sound affects with the creepy music that plays when getting chased is a good example to watch where you are going.If I had to make one complaint about the game then that would be the length. For a horror game it is very shortened down and as for the scary experience that you have throughtout the game, it only lasts for a few hours on a normal based difficulty. Thats where the DLC comes in to action. The Whistleblower DLC adds a new character and longer storyline to play when you have completed the original!The DLC - called Whistleblower - The Whistleblower DLC is a great add-on for the game. It adds a nice, new and longer story for people that want to carry on playing Outlast and have already completed the Original game. On Whistleblower you play the character ""Waylon Park"". This game is a sequal to the Original but Whistleblower storyline stretches out from the Original in the ending.As it stands - Outlast is my favourite all-time horror game for me, it has all the scary features in it for me. Jumpscares are perfect along with the Sound effects. Hope they make more awesome horror games like this"
