,Recommended,238320,8465933,"Posted: 31 December, 2013",all,Dr. Freeman,"I have been a horror buff since I was a child. I've played horror games since the original Resident Evil and honestly, most horror games in the present don't impress me much (Amnesia: A Machine For Pigs), but this game ""Outlast"" has changed my outlook entirely for the survival horror genre. The game from start lets you in control of everything that can happen to you. The game doesn't let you catch a break ""ever"". You are constantly on edge of your seat in alertness wondering what is around the corner.              The coolest part about this game is how the story is unfolded. The beggining gives you a summary as to ""why"" you are there. That is all. The rest of the story is up to you, to record, discover, and explore the asylum in order to actually ""know"" what is going on. They give very good use of the camera recorder and make it your most valuable tool. I won't explain the horror of the game, you just need to buy this for yourself. It is in my opinion the best horror game I have played since the original amnesia launch, which outlast makes Amnesia look like Kittyland. I give this game a 10/10. Perfect score. PS: The immersion is flawless, if you are into roleplay, this game will suit your needs perfectly! Enjoy this game in the dark! Good luck."
