,Recommended,238320,27684,"Posted: 7 September, 2013",all,Zeke,"This game was $15 for me and it lasted 5 hours. Now here's the kicker: It's worth that $15, or even, 20 dollars for it. Just think for a second: Do you want a horror game that will scare you like Amnesia did, but a hell of a lot better? If you answered yes, you should get this game.But lemme praise 3 things about it before I do the cons. First, the first person view is actually first person view. You see your hands, shadow, etc. There's even proper head bobbing. Normally first person games tend to render the hands with no lower half. This game really makes you feel like you're a person. Second thing: The camera works fine, but only loses battery power when you use the night vision. Batteries means you can't keep nightvision on 100% of the time and it puts pressure on you. Third is roaming enemies. In Amnesia, the monsters would give up and vanish. In Outlast, they keep looking for you, which makes getting from room A to room B a lot harder, knowing that they are STILL out there.As for complains, I wish the game was a little longer. Also, the  two ""naked brothers"" should have been in the game more. Yeah, I'll let that image sink in.This game goes out of its way to scare you and it doesrather well. I wonder how Amnesia: A Machine for Pigs will fair after playing Outlast."
