76561197972234665,Recommended,238320,31576430,Posted: 6 May,all,Flori der Fux,"I think everything has been said about Outlast, so I'll keep my review short. This is by far the best and scariest horror game that I played in a very long long time.  It is technically very well made. Fantastic graphics and sounds, stable frame rates, found no bugs, responsive controls. The gameplay can best be compared to Amnesia, but in my opinion Outlast is doing everything better, in all aspects. This feeling of doom and helplessness is just fantstic. You never know what awaits you behind the next corner and horror and insanity are ever present. And yet Outlast is surprisingly fair at all times. I've never come across any frustrating moments where frustration kills horror. So yet I've died a few times but that's been my fault as there have always been realistic chances for me to escape or hide. Only the story is a bit thin and weak, especially the ending, which is why I definitely recommend playing the DLC ""Whistleblower"" as well. There, a lot of questions are being answered, and it provides a satisfying ending as well. It took me almost 13 hours to finish main game and DLC. It's probably possible to rush through the game much faster, but those 13 hours felt perfect for me - not one minute too long, not one minute too short. It's an intense game, a brilliant game, and definitely worth each cent!"
