76561197994346855,Recommended,238320,9675083,"Posted: 30 March, 2014",all,gloken40k,"I gave this game a thumbs up, but I struggled with that decision.  If you can catch this game at a SERIOUS discount ( less than $5 ), then it's a decent deal.  Otherwise, do not pay full price for this game.  I'm not giving any spoilers, but this game is SHORT.  I think I got through it in about 5 hours, with some AFK time padded in there, and there is no replay value whatsoever, unless you feel like being a completionist.  Or unless they come out with a sequel and you're looking to refresh your memory on the story.The game does have its good points.  If you're into a strange story, eerie feels, and lots of darkness, then this game is for you.  Graphics and sound are surprisingly good, and there were definitely a few points in the game where I jumped.  It's a first-person perspective and done mostly in the tradition of movies such as the Blair Witch Project, or Paranormal Activity.  The rest of the goodies I'll leave up to you to discover.Conclusively, again this is a very short game, but if they come out with a decent sequel to follow this game up, it might be worth it to pick this up on a decent Steam sale.(Disclaimer:  I don't hold any arguments about dollar per hour of entertainment as valid.  A short game is not worth as much to me as a longer game in 99% of cases.  Your opinion may differ.  GL&HF)"
